BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-trainer-form@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260522
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260523
SUMMARY:⚙ Trainer session — barbell form (squat\, RDL\, hip thrust)
DESCRIPTION:Non-negotiable per plan §gym before Gym A in week 3. One 60-min
  session\, filmed from side + front. Cues for back squat depth and knee tr
 acking\, RDL hip hinge\, hip thrust setup. NOK 800–1200.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-gym-membership@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260524
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260525
SUMMARY:⚙ Gym membership active (SATS / Family Sports / Stamina)
DESCRIPTION:Gym A starts plan week 3 (week of May 25). Pick one this week.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-hrmax-test@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260530
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260531
SUMMARY:⌖ HRmax field test
DESCRIPTION:10 min easy w/u + 3 × 3 min uphill all-out\, 2 min jog recovery
 . Highest reading in third rep ≈ true max. Sets every zone downstream\; bl
 ind without it. Plan week 3.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-garmin-zones@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:⚙ Override Garmin HR zones to %HRR (Karvonen) after HRmax test
DESCRIPTION:Garmin Connect → User Settings → Heart Rate → Manual. Z1 50–60%
  HRR\, Z2 60–70%\, Z3 70–80% (top of Z3 = 75–78% = sub-threshold ceiling)\
 , Z4 80–90% (STAY OUT)\, Z5 90–100% (never go here). Structured workouts p
 ushed to the Fenix will carry wrong targets otherwise.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-hrrest-baseline@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260517
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260518
SUMMARY:⌖ 3-morning HRrest baseline (lie still on wake\, watch reading)
DESCRIPTION:Plan week 1 task. Anchors readiness traffic-light thresholds.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:to27-task-parkrun-benchmark@training
DTSTAMP:20260515T085337Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:⌖ Porsgrunn parkrun 5K — sub-threshold pace anchor
DESCRIPTION:Anchors sub-threshold pace (= 5K pace + 35–45 sec/km). Backup i
 f weather kills parkrun: 5K best-effort treadmill at 1% grade\, fresh legs
 \, same week.
END:VEVENT
